---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
export const prerender = true;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Miller Trust Guide"
  description="What data we collect, what we don't, and how we handle email addresses and payment data."
>
  <article class="prose-content mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted">Last updated 2026-07-11.</p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Email address</strong> — at checkout (to deliver the kit) and optionally via the lead-magnet form (to
        send the free educational PDF and a 30–45-day educational email sequence you can unsubscribe from at any time).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Payment information</strong> — handled entirely by Stripe. We never see your card number. Stripe stores
        the transaction record per its own retention policy (≥7 years).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Consent acknowledgment</strong> — the checkout consent record (timestamp + IP) is stored in our server
        logs and in Stripe's order metadata.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Aggregate analytics</strong> via Vercel Web Analytics — no cookies, no personally identifying
        information; pageview counts and referrer URLs only.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Search-ad conversion measurement.</strong> When we run search ads, the ad platform's conversion tag
        (Google's <code>gtag.js</code>, and Microsoft's if enabled) loads on our pages and may set a first-party cookie
        so we can tell whether an ad click led to a purchase. On a completed purchase it reports the sale amount and an
        opaque order id — never your name, email, or any family or financial details. We use it only to measure whether
        our ads work; we do not retarget you or build a profile. Details in
        <a href="#advertising-measurement">Advertising measurement</a> below.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we do NOT collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not ask for the applicant's name, income, Social Security number, age, family situation, or any other personal information about your family.</li>
      <li>We do not run behavioral profiling tools, and we do not use advertising cookies to retarget you or build a profile of you. The only third-party tag we run is the search-ad conversion tag described above — and only to measure whether an ad led to a sale.</li>
      <li>We do not maintain user accounts. There is no login.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we do with email addresses</h2>
    <p>
      Buyer email addresses are used only to deliver the kit, send refund confirmations, and respond to support
      requests. Lead-magnet emails are used to send the educational nurture sequence and a soft kit pitch at the end.
      You can unsubscribe from the nurture sequence at any time via the link in every email.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>We do not sell or share email addresses</strong> with attorneys, Medicaid planners, lead-generation
      companies, advertisers, affiliates, or any third party. Ever.
    </p>

    <h2 id="advertising-measurement">Advertising measurement</h2>
    <p>
      We may run ads on Google Search (and later Microsoft/Bing). So we don't waste money on ads that don't work, we use
      the ad platform's standard conversion tag to learn whether an ad click actually led to a kit purchase. Precisely
      what that involves:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Google's tag (<code>gtag.js</code>) loads on our pages and may store a first-party cookie remembering that you arrived from an ad.</li>
      <li>When a purchase completes, we tell the ad platform that a sale happened, its dollar amount, and an opaque order reference. We do <strong>not</strong> send your name, email, or any information about your family or finances.</li>
      <li>We do not use this to retarget you with ads elsewhere, and we do not build a behavioral profile of you.</li>
      <li>You can manage ad personalization at <a href="https://myadcenter.google.com" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Google My Ad Center</a>, and you can block cookies in your browser at any time — it will not affect your ability to buy or download a kit.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Service providers</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — payment processing and tax calculation.</li>
      <li><strong>Resend</strong> — transactional email (order receipts, kit download links) and the educational email sequence for lead-magnet subscribers.</li>
      <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — site hosting, file storage for the kit PDF, and cookie-less analytics.</li>
      <li><strong>Google</strong> — search-ad conversion measurement only (the conversion tag described in <a href="#advertising-measurement">Advertising measurement</a>); we do not sell or share your data with Google for any other purpose.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      To request deletion of your email address from our records, email <a href="mailto:support@millertrustguide.com">support@millertrustguide.com</a>.
      We honor deletion requests within 7 business days. Note that Stripe retains order records independently per its
      own retention policy and we cannot delete those.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p><a href="mailto:support@millertrustguide.com">support@millertrustguide.com</a></p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
